1 VEHICLE RIDERS AND RECREATIONAL ACTIVITIES ON LANDS MANAGED PRIMARILY
2 FOR OFF–HIGHWAY RECREATIONAL VEHICLE USE;
3 (4) AT LEAST 5% OF THE ANNUAL FUND BALANCE SHALL BE USED TO
4 LEASE LANDS FOR PUBLIC OFF–HIGHWAY RECREATIONAL VEHICLE USE;
5 (5) AT LEAST 10% OF THE ANNUAL FUND BALANCE SHALL BE
6 AUTHORIZED TO ADVERTISE, PROMOTE, AND MARKET OFF–HIGHWAY
7 RECREATIONAL VEHICLE USE AND EDUCATION IN THE STATE; AND
8 (6) FUNDS FROM THE FUND SHALL BE USED TO COVER THE
9 ADMINISTRATIVE AND OPERATING COSTS OF THE BOARD.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the terms of the initial
11 appointed members of the Off–Highway Recreational Vehicle Recreation Oversight Board
12 established under Section 1 of this Act shall expire as follows:
13 (1) one member in 2026;
14 (2) two members in 2027; and
15 (3) two members in 2028.
16 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
17 October 1, 2025.
